rls!]]''\n| opening theme \"7 Girls War\"\n|-\n| ''[[Captain Earth]]''\n| insert song \"Mugen no Hana\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"6\" | 2016\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Kizumonogatari (film series)|Kizumonogatari Part 1: Tekketsu]]''\n| with Ryuichi Takada, Keigo Hoashi, and [[Ken Namba]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Monogatari (series)|Koyomimonogatari]]''\n| \n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Monster Strike (anime)|Monster Strike]]''\n| with Keiichi Hirokawa and Kuniyuki Takahashi\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Anne Happy]]''\n| with various others\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Kizumonogatari (film series)|Kizumonogatari Part 2: Nekketsu]]''\n| & ending theme \"\u00e9toile et toi\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Monster Strike The Movie|Monster Strike The Movie]]''\n| with Kuniyuki Takahashi, Ryuichi Takada, and Keiichi Hirokawa\n|-\n|-\n! rowspan=\"5\" | 2017\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Kizumonogatari (film series)|Kizumonogatari Part 3: Reiketsu]]''\n| & ending theme \"\u00e9toile et toi [\u00e9dition le blanc]\"\n|-\n| ''[[Frame Arms Girl]]''\n| opening theme \"Tiny Tiny\"\n|-\n| ''[[Monogatari (series)|Owarimonogatari ]]''\n| & opening themes \"terminal terminal\" and \"dreamy date drive\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Fireworks (2017 film)|Fireworks]]''\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Wake Up, Girls!|Wake Up, Girls! New Chapter]]''\n| insert song \"Kakeru x Kakeru\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"1\" | 2018\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Fate/Extra Last Encore]]''\n| & opening theme \"Bright Burning Shout\"; with Kakeru Ishihama, Keigo Hoashi, Ryuichi Takada, and Ken Namba\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | 2019\n| ''[[Monogatari (series)|Zoku Owarimonogatari]]''\n| opening theme \"07734\"\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Beastars]]''\n| & ending themes \"Le Zoo\" and \"Floating Story on the Moon\"; insert songs \"Many Stories\" and \"A Tale of Moon\"; with Ryuichi Takada\n|-\n! rowspan=\"1\" | 2020\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Maesetsu!]]''<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sherman |first1=Jennifer |title=High School Fleet's Yuu Nobuta Directs Original Maesetsu! Anime |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-01/high-school-fleet-yuu-nobuta-directs-original-maesetsu-anime/.152878 |website = [[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=16 February 2020 |date=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n| with Monaca\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Video games ===\n{{legend2|#bbffbb|Background music composition|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#F9F9F9|Other credits only (e.g. performances, insert songs)|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title<ref name=\"monaca\" />\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n! rowspan=\"1\" | 1999\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[List of Namco games#Namco console-based systems|Aqua Rush]]''\n| with Akitaka Tohyama and Yoshihito Yano\n|-ra\n! rowspan=\"1\" | 2000\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Tekken Tag Tournament]]''\n| & trumpet; with various others\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | 2001\n| ''[[Mr._Driller#Titles|Mr. Driller G]]''\n| trumpet\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Tekken 4]]''\n| arcade version; with [[Yuu Miyake]] and Akitaka Tohyama\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Kotoba no Puzzle: Mojipittan]]''\n| & various insert songs, lyrics, vocals\n|-\n! rowspan=\"3\" | 2002\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''Tekken 4''\n| PS2 version; with Yuu Miyake, Akitaka Tohyama, Hiroshi Okubo, and Keiki Kobayashi\n|-\n| ''[[Taiko no Tatsujin|Taiko no Tatsujin 3]]''\n| trumpet\n|-\n| ''[[Mr. Driller Drill Land]]''\n| trumpet\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | 2003\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Yumeria]]''\n| & trumpet, [[melodica]]\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[R: Racing Evolution]]''\n| with Yuu Miyake, Hiroshi Okubo, Akitaka Tohyama, and Koji Nakagawa\n|-\n! rowspan=\"4\" | 2004\n| ''[[Katamari Damacy]]''\n| trumpet\n|-\n| style=\"background:#bbffbb;\" | ''[[Xenosaga#Additional media|Xenosaga Freaks]]''