 p.516</ref>\n|| 3,171\n|\n* [[80th Regiment Indiana Infantry|80th Indiana]]: Ltc Lewis Brooks\n* [[50th Ohio Infantry|50th Ohio]]: Col Jonah R. Taylor,<ref>Fled the field at the onset of battle</ref> Ltc Silas A. Strickland\n* [[98th Ohio Infantry|98th Ohio]]: Ltc Christian L. Poorman\n* [[121st Ohio Infantry|121st Ohio]]: Col William Pitt Reid\n* [[19th Independent Battery Indiana Light Artillery|19th Indiana Battery Light Artillery]] [4 12-pdr How, 2 3\" R]: Cpt Samuel J. Harris\n|-\n|}\n\n===[[II Corps (Union Army)|II Corps]]===\n<small>20,000 men, 65 guns (k-2, w-4, m-6 = 12)</small>\n\nMG [[Thomas Leonidas Crittenden]]\n\nEscort:\n* [[1st Regiment Michigan Volunteer Engineers and Mechanics|1st Michigan Engineers & Mechanics]] (Companies B, E, I, & K): Col William Power Innes\n* [[1st Ohio Cavalry]] (4 companies): Maj James Laughlin\n* [[3rd Ohio Cavalry]] (4 companies): Maj John Howard Foster\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:90%;\"\n! width=20% | Division\n! width=20% | Brigade\n! width=5% | Strength\n! width=45% | Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nFourth Division<br />\n<small>27 guns, k-0, w-0, m-0 = 0</small>\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[William Sooy Smith]]<br>[[File:William Sooy Smith.jpg|thumb|center|upright=0.3|Smith]]\n\n<br />\nEscort:\n* 2nd Kentucky Cavalry (4 companies): Ltc Thomas Cochran\n| 10th Brigade\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[William Grose]]\n|| 2,152\n|\n* [[84th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|84th Illinois]]: Col Louis H. Waters\n* [[36th Regiment Indiana Infantry|36th Indiana]]: Ltc Oliver Hazard Perry Cary\n* [[23rd Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|23rd Kentucky]]: Ltc John P. Jackson\n* [[6th Ohio Infantry|6th Ohio]]: Col [[Nicholas Longworth Anderson]]\n* [[24th Ohio Infantry|24th Ohio]]: Ltc Frederick C. Jones\n* [[4th U.S. Light Artillery, Battery H|4th US Light Artillery, Battery \"H\"]] [4 12-pdr Nap, 2 10-pdr Par]: Bvt Lt Samuel Canby\n* [[4th U.S. Light Artillery, Battery M|4