e, October 8, 1862'' (Revised January 10, 2008), unpublished paper, [[Perryville Battlefield State Historic Site]].\n* {{cite book|ref=harv |last=Noe |first=Kenneth W. |title=Perryville: This Grand Havoc of Battle |publisher=University Press of Kentucky |year=2001 |location=Lexington, Ky. |isbn=978-0-8131-2209-0 }}\n* U.S. War Department, [http://cdl.library.cornell.edu/moa/browse.monographs/waro.html ''The War of the Rebellion'']: ''A Compilation of the [[Official Records of the American Civil War|Official Records]] of the Union and Confederate Armies'', Series I, Volume XVI, Part I and II (Washington, DC:  U.S. Government Printing Office), 1886.\n\n{{Kentucky in the Civil War}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Perryville Union Order Of Battle}}\n[[Category:American Civil War orders of battle]]\n", "text_old": "The following [[Union Army]] units and commanders fought in the [[Battle of Perryville]] of the [[American Civil War]]. Order of battle compiled from the army organization<ref>Official Records, Series I, Volume XVI, Part 2, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;idno=waro0023;node=waro0023%3A3;view=image;seq=593;size=100 pages 591-596].</ref><ref>Multiple commander names indicate command succession of command during the battle or the campaign.</ref> during the battle and return of casualties.<ref>Official Records, Series I, Volume XVI, Part 1, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0022&node=waro0022%3A8&view=image&seq=1047&size=100 pages 1033-1036].</ref> The [[Perryville Confederate order of battle|Confederate order of battle]] is listed separately.\n\n==Abbreviations used==\n\n===Military rank===\n* '''MG''' = [[Major general (United States)|Major General]]\n* '''BG''' = [[Brigadier general (United States)|Brigadier General]]\n* '''Col''' = [[Colonel (United States)|Colonel]]\n* '''Ltc''' = [[Lieutenant Colonel (United States)|Lieutenant Colonel]]\n* '''Maj''' = [[Major (United States)|Major]]\n* '''Cpt''' = [[Captain (United States O-3)|Captain]]\n* '''Lt''' =  [[1st Lieutenant#U.S. Army.2C U.S. Marine Corps and U.S. Air Force|1st Lieutenant]]\n* '''2Lt''' = [[Second Lieutenant#United States|2nd Lieutenant]]\n* '''Sgt''' = [[Sergeant#American Civil War|Sergeant]]\n* '''Bvt''' = [[Brevet (military)|Brevet]]\n\n===Artillery===\n* '''10-pdr Par''' = [[10-pounder Parrott rifle]]\n* '''12-pdr How''' = [[M1841 12-pounder howitzer]]\n* '''12-pdr Mtn''' = [[M1841 mountain howitzer]]\n* '''12-pdr Nap''' = M1857 [[12-pounder Napoleon]]\n* '''24-pdr How''' = M1841 24-pounder howitzer\n* '''3\" R'''       = [[3-inch Ordnance rifle]]\n* '''6-pdr SB'''   = [[M1841 6-pounder field gun]]\n* '''Jam R'''      = [[James rifle]]\n* '''How'''        = [[Field artillery in the American Civil War#Howitzers|howitzer]]\n* '''pdr'''        = [[Pound (mass)|pound]] ([[projectile]] weight)\n* '''R'''          = [[Field artillery in the American Civil War#Rifled guns|rifled gun]]\n* '''SB'''         = [[Field artillery in the American Civil War#Guns|smoothbore gun]]\n\n===Other===\n* '''w''' = [[Wounded in action|wounded]]\n* '''mw''' = [[Mortal wound|mortally wounded]]\n* '''k''' = [[Killed in action|killed]]\n* '''c''' = [[Prisoner of war|captured]]\n* '''m''' = [[Missing in action|missing]]\n\n==[[Army of the Ohio]]==\n<small>55,000 men, 147 guns (k-889, w-2966, m-433 = 4,288)</small><br />\n<br />\nMG [[Don Carlos Buell]], Commanding<br />\nMG [[George Henry Thomas]], second in command<br />\n<br />\nEscort:\n* [[Anderson Troop]], Pennsylvania Cavalry: 2Lt Thomas S. Maple\n* [[4th Cavalry Regiment (United States)|4th US Cavalry]] (Companies B, C, D, G, I, & K): Ltc James Oakes\n<br />\nSignal detachment: Cpt Jesse Merrill\n\n===[[I Corps (Union Army)|I Corps]]===\n<small>13,000 men, 38 guns (k-695, w-2290, m-346 = 3,331)</small>\n\nMG [[Alexander McDowell McCook]]\n\n* Chief of Staff: Ltc [[James Vote Bomford]] ('''w''')\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: