ed Smith Fry]]\n|| 2,391\n|\n* [[10th Regiment Indiana Infantry|10th Indiana]]: Col William Coalbaugh Kise\n* [[74th Regiment Indiana Infantry|74th Indiana]]: Col Charles Warner Chapman\n* [[4th Kentucky Volunteer Regiment|4th Kentucky]]: Col [[John T. Croxton|John Thomas Croxton]]\n* [[10th Regiment Kentucky Volunteer Infantry|10th Kentucky]]: Ltc [[William Hercules Hays]]\n* [[14th Ohio Infantry|14th Ohio]]: Ltc George P. Este\n* [[Battery C, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light Artillery, Battery \"C\"]] [2 12-pdr How, 4 6-pdr M1841 Jam R]: Cpt Daniel K. Southwick\n|-\n|3rd Brigade\n<small>k-0, w-7, m-7 = 14</small>\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[James B. Steedman|James Blair Steedman]]\n|| 3,043\n|\n* [[87th Regiment Indiana Infantry|87th Indiana]]: Col Kline Godfrey Shryock\n* [[2nd Minnesota Volunteer Infantry|2nd Minnesota]]: Col James George\n* [[9th Ohio Infantry|9th Ohio]]: Ltc Charles Joseph\n* [[35th Ohio Infantry|35th Ohio]]: Col [[Ferdinand Van Derveer]]\n* [[18th Infantry Regiment (United States)|18th US]]: Maj Frederick Townsend\n* [[4th U.S. Light Artillery, Battery I|4th US Light Artillery, Battery \"I\"]] [4 12-pdr How]: Lt Frank G. Smith\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nNinth Division<br />\n<small>16 guns, k-133, w-356, m-58 = 547</small>\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Robert Byington Mitchell]]<br>[[File:Robert Byington Mitchell.jpg|thumb|center|upright=0.3|Mitchell]]\n\n<br />\nEscort:\n* [[Independent Illinois Volunteer Cavalry Companies|Sherer's Independent Cavalry Company]]: Cpt Samuel B. Sherer\n* [[2nd Regiment Kansas Volunteer Cavalry|2nd Kansas Cavalry]] (detachment, 150 men): Sgt Hugh Quinn\n| 30th Brigade\n<small>k-133, w-344, m-58 = 535</small>\n\n<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Michael Gooding ('''w'''/'''c''')\n|| 1,423\n|\n* [[59th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|59th Illinois]]: Maj Joshua Carroll Winters\n* [[74th Illinois Volunteer Infantry Regiment|74th Illinois]]: Col James B. Kerr (not engaged; supply train guard)\n* [[75th Illinoi